.index.container
  .row
    .col-xs-12
      h1 Show your package user base
  .row
    .col-xs-12
      label.control-label(for="repository_url") Get the badge:
      form.js-repository-form
        .input-group
          input.form-control.js-repository-url(id="repository_url" type="text" placeholder="Repository URL (e.g. \"https://github.com/spirehq/github-users-badge-api\")")
          span.input-group-btn
            button.btn.btn-primary(type="submit") Get badge
        label.js-error-message.control-label(for="repository_url" style="display: none;")
  .row
    .col-xs-12
      .result
        .badge-wrapper.text-center
          a(href=detailsUrl)
            img(src=path)
        .panel.panel-default
          .panel-heading
            h3.panel-title Great job! Now add it to your <a href="{{readmeUrl}}">README.md</a>:
          .panel-body
            p Show your package user base:
            textarea.form-control.insert-code(readonly="readonly") {{insertCode}}
  .row
    .col-xs-12
      hr
  .row
    .col-xs-12
      h2 FAQ
      #accordion.panel-group(role='tablist', aria-multiselectable='true')
        .panel.panel-default
          #headingOne.panel-heading(role='tab')
            h4.panel-title
              a.collapsed(role='button', data-toggle='collapse', data-parent='#accordion', href='#collapseOne', aria-expanded='true', aria-controls='collapseOne')
                | How is it different from NPM's "dependents" metric?
          #collapseOne.panel-collapse.collapse(role='tabpanel', aria-labelledby='headingOne')
            .panel-body
              p Here's a good example based on "grunt-processhtml" package:
              ul
                li
                  a(href="https://www.npmjs.com/browse/depended/grunt-processhtml" target="_blank") <strong>7</strong> dependents
                li
                  a(href="https://github.com/search?utf8=âœ“&q=grunt-processhtml+filename%3Apackage.json&type=Code&ref=searchresults" target="_blank") <strong>3,450</strong> mentions
              p That's ~500x difference :)
